Clear skies- quite breezy (but better than the last couple of days)air temp 58*F- water temp 53*F.  No other people on the water- but saw 3 geese and 3 ducks.  Feeling like coming fall.
Clear day with light breeze- no other people or animals on the water.

Light breeze-clear skies- n o boats- people or animals observed.  Air temp in mid 60*'s F. Light breeze-clear skies- n o boats- people or animals observed.  Air temp in mid 60*'s F.  Water level is very high again.  Another 2+ inches of rain over past few days.
A cloudy and hazy day air temp 72*F- water 68*F.  No other people out- but 3 ducks- 1 eagle and 1 loon were observed.

column1: My last day of data collecting this year- including temperature at depth/dissolved oxygen.  Water is once again very high.

column2: Norm and Nancy Hahn were the collectors today- their last time for 2019- they're heading back south tomorrow :(

column1: It was a cloudy- cool day-55*F- with a few sprinkles of rain- light breeze and chop.  No one else out- human or wildlife.
Water level continues extremely high.

column2: Sunny- cool-upper 50's- windy.  One other boat out.  Our last secchi collection of the 2019 season ! We were unable to go out on 10/5 or 10/6 due to rain.  Water is very stirred up- water level is still very high.
FIrst quality check for 2020 season.  Sunny- light breeze- water temp 58*F-air temp- mid 60's.  4 boats on the water.
What a difference 10 days make ! Partly cloudy- light breeze- ripples on water air temp 78*F- water temp 74 *F.  A shower had just passed by about 15 minutes earlier.  No one else on the water.
Sunny day- air temp low 80'sF- water 70*F. Slight breeze and ripple on the water.  No other boats or wildlife observed.
Partly cloudy- air temp low 80'sF- water temp 74*F.  Light breeze- light ripple on surface of water- No boats- no wildlife observed.

Karyl and her cousin JoAnne did the monitoring on this beautiful sunny June afternoon- with light winds and some chop- but no big waves. The air temp was in the mid 80'sF water surface temp 70*F at mid lake.  No other boats- but an eagle flew over and several families were out on their piers with multi-generational groups having fun .

Sharon and Karyl went out today- a pleasant day with air temp in low 70's and water temp about 76*. Fair skies with light wind. 2 other boats out on the water and we saw the adult eagle on the nest taking care of the chick- who is growing fast.

Sharon and Karyl went out together today- a lovely morning with fair skies and light wind.  Air temperature was about 72*F- water temp at surface 76*F. 2 other boats were out- one cruising- one with fishers.  We saw our adult eagle on the nest on the island with its chick.
Sunny and hot day- air temp already 83*F- water temp at mid lake nearly the same. Lots of boats out-cruising- tubing- and also 2 jet skis. Typical Independence Day weekend !
Karyl's cousins JoAnne- Lucie and Megan Streit did the data collection today. Air temp was about 80*F- water temp low 80's*F. Light wind- one other boat on the lake.
Bill Rosenberg helped collect and record data today.  Air temperature was about 84*F- water at surface was 82*F.

column1: Fair sky- moderate breeze.  One other boat seen.

column2: Temp at depth and dissolved oxygen were done today- 7/20/2020 due to sensor problems on 7/17/2020.  No secchi readings taken on 7/20/20.   Air temp 72*F- partly sunny sky with many alto cumulus clouds.  Two other boats on the water. Only temp. at depth and dissolved oxygen was collected today due to equipment problems on 7/17.

column1: Secchi data listed is the same as recorded on 7/17.  Other observations for 7/20 are as follows:
Air temp 72*F- mostly cloudy with alto cumulus clouds most common.  Moderate breeze.  2 other boats on the water- one pulling a tuber.

column2: Glenn Johnson and grandson Percy Johnson were the actual collectors today.  Cloudy skies- windy air and water temperature 72*F.   One other boat was out on the water.

My cousins JoAnne and Ken Streit used their boat to go out and collect data today. A sunny afternoon- light north breeze- air temp 65*F- water about 73*F.  No one else- human or wildlife were observed. My cousins JoAnne and Ken Streit used their boat to go out and collect data today. A sunny afternoon- light north breeze- air temp 65*F- water about 73*F.  No one else- human or wildlife were observed.

Thank you to my cousins Ken and Megan Streit for doing the Secchi disk readings today !  What a nice calm morning they had on the water after yesterday's wild and windy day.  No other boats or wildlife were observed.  The sky was sunny and the air temperature 70*F.
Karyl and her cousin Cindy went out to collect data today.  Partly cloudy-light wind- air temp 80*F- water temp 82*F.

column1: One other boat- no wildlife.  We wanted to do both secchi and DO/Temp at depth today- but alas- the sensor refused to cooperate. So sad.

column2: Today my other cousin Jim joined me to learn how data is collected.  Getting more family members involved all the time ! It is a cloudy- breezy humid day- seems like a front is sorta hanging over us and we're on the warmer side. Air temp is 80*F- water at surface 76*F. No other boats were out- but we saw a young muskrat swimming and this year's eagle offspring high in his tree- calling out to mom as usual.  Happily- we had Sandy Wichman's DO/Temp at depth kit today and it worked well.

Sharon and Karyl worked together on both secchi and phosphorous/chlorophyll collection.  A very chilly day- air temp 50*F- water 62*F.  Overcast with very light breeze.  No other boats- but two loons were observed. Feels like fall !

Glenn Johnson did the monitoring today.  The air temp was 64*F and so was the water.  Partly cloudy- nice day overall. One other boat was out as was one loon. Trees are beginning to show some fall colors- especially in the inlet creek area.
Lovely first day of fall.  Clear skies- light wind- air 73*F- water 68*F. Trees are starting to change color- no other people on the lake- one loon and one eagle seen eating a fish on a log.
Glenn Johnson was the actual collector today. Air temp 42*F- Water 60*F.  Overcast- breezy. Color seems to be at peak.

Karyl and Sharon did our last collection of the 2020 season on a cool- sunny day with light winds. Air temperature is about 60*F- water 56*F. The last several windy days have really stirred the water up- the first time this season it looks cloudy/murky. The colors are probably on their last few days- definitely more muted than the last 2 weeks- but still lovely. We were the only ones on the water human or wild and the "TDL Research Vessel " made it's way to the boat landing to come out for the winter.  Our season is over- thanks to the wonderful Water Quality Team for all their efforts this year.
